articles.author: Harry Baker
articles.title: 10 bizarre 'dark voids' appear in the skies over uninhabited island near Antarctica — Earth from space - Live Science
articles.description: A 2016 satellite photo shows nearly a dozen swirling dark spots that emerged in the clouds over Heard Island in the Indian Ocean.
articles.content:
Where is it? Heard Island, Indian Ocean [-53.116414344, 73.51793263]
What's in the photo? An unusual stream of von Kármán vortices trailing off a hidden peak
